  "text": "Quantitative data on service utilization were abstracted from the national health information system at the district level. Given the complexity of factors related to caesareans [CITATION_1] , we focused on assisted deliveries in CSPSs and CMAs, where the policy's impacts are more readily observable. We obtained secondary data from eight health districts, for a total of 211 health facilities. To assess trends, we produced time series of the mean monthly number of deliveries by CSPS between January 2004 and September 2009 (69 months) after calculating fifth-order moving averages.",
